\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {5}{\ignorespaces NIST SP\nonbreakingspace 800-90B final min-entropy assessment (\texttt  {ea\_non\_iid}, byte-level, 99\% confidence). WiFi CSI achieves 5.50\nonbreakingspace bpb (69\% of theoretical maximum), compared to 6.35 for IBM Quantum (ibm\_kingston, 156\nonbreakingspace qubits) and 6.36 for \texttt  {os.urandom}. The CSI result is the first SP\nonbreakingspace 800-90B assessment of WiFi CSI data.}}{8}{figure.caption.29}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:minentropy-bars}{{5}{8}{NIST SP~800-90B final min-entropy assessment (\texttt {ea\_non\_iid}, byte-level, 99\% confidence). WiFi CSI achieves 5.50~bpb (69\% of theoretical maximum), compared to 6.35 for IBM Quantum (ibm\_kingston, 156~qubits) and 6.36 for \texttt {os.urandom}. The CSI result is the first SP~800-90B assessment of WiFi CSI data}{figure.caption.29}{}}
