\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {6}{\ignorespaces Extraction quality vs.\ number of input frames. Both extraction ratio (solid, left axis) and min-entropy (dashed, right axis) converge with increasing sample size. Our measurement (343\nonbreakingspace frames, circled) yields 24.5\% and 5.50\nonbreakingspace bpb. Extrapolation to 1{,}000 frames suggests marginal improvement to $\approx $5.65\nonbreakingspace bpb, still below quantum and OS sources.}}{8}{figure.caption.30}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:extraction-sensitivity}{{6}{8}{Extraction quality vs.\ number of input frames. Both extraction ratio (solid, left axis) and min-entropy (dashed, right axis) converge with increasing sample size. Our measurement (343~frames, circled) yields 24.5\% and 5.50~bpb. Extrapolation to 1{,}000 frames suggests marginal improvement to $\approx $5.65~bpb, still below quantum and OS sources}{figure.caption.30}{}}
